# 8. 贈り合う想い

Tsukasa: Alright, it looks like we're all here.
Tsukasa: This is Rui's and my way of thanking all of you for everything that you do day to day. Enjoy, and bon appetit!
Emu: Wow...! These cookies all have pictures on them!
Rui: We used icing on them. Each one has a unique design and message on it. Take any that suit your fancy.
Nene: Oh, right... Today's White Day, huh?
Miku: Wow☆ This one has a Ferris wheel on it! And this one has a merry-go-round!
Rin: That's so cool☆ I can't decide which to choose.
Emu: Thanks, Tsukasa, Rui!
Emu: So, I also have something that I wanna give all of you.
Tsukasa: Give us?
Emu: Ta-daa! I wrote message cards to show just how much I appreciate all of you guys☆
Emu: Starting with you, Tsukasa! Here's yours!
Tsukasa: Oh...! I'd heard that you went to help out with an event involving making cards, but I wasn't expecting to receive one...
Tsukasa: Thank you very much! Hm...? All these star stickers...
Tsukasa: Ah, I see! They must represent the shining star that I am!
Emu: Ding ding ding!
Emu: I'm always encouraged by the way you do your absolute best every day! This is my way of thanking you for that!
Tsukasa: I could say the same for you, Emu. Let us both keep moving forward down the path to stardom!
Emu: Yeah!
Emu: Next is... Rui! Here you are!
Rui: Thank you. Hehe. Mine has robots and a jack-in-the-box on it.
Emu: Hehe. That's because you're always making robots and coming up with fun effects that surprise the audience☆
Emu: Thanks for everything, Rui!
Rui: Thank you as well. I'm constantly inspired by your sheer athletic talent and free imagination.
Emu: Next! Drum roll please... Here's your card, Nene!
Nene: Wow, these stickers are really cute... Musical notes, and a princess singing a song?
Emu: Yup! Because you're always making lots and lots of people smile with your beautiful singing voice!
Nene: Emu...
Emu: And thank you for always hanging out with me! Let's go grab some taiyaki again in the future!
Nene: Hehe. I'd love to... Let's hang out again soon.
Emu: Next are my cards for everyone in SEKAI!
Luka: Oh, you made cards for us?
MEIKO: Hehe. That's so nice of you! Let's form a line, shall we?
Len & Rin: Woohoo!
Saki: Alright, I'd like to begin our fun and exciting message card exchange party!
Ichika: We heard that we were going to be making our own message cards and exchanging them with each other...
Miku: But how are we actually supposed to make our cards?
Rin: Heh heh heh. Don't worry. We'll teach you guys everything that you need to know!
Saki: Right! Starting with you, Ichi!
Ichika: O-Okay...!
Saki: I made your card in the shape of a guitar!
Ichika: Oh, look at that... It even has cactus stickers on it.
Saki: “I really admire how you're so passionate about what you do, Ichi.”
Saki: “When you decide to do something, you just move straight toward it. You don't know how many times you've helped me by doing that.”
Ichika: Saki...
Saki: “I'm really glad that you're my friend, so thank you! I hope we get to be besties forever and ever!”
Ichika: Thanks, Saki... You've also been a huge source of support for me.
Ichika: I really appreciate you making this card for me. I promise to cherish it.
Rin: Alright, I wanna go next!
Rin: Who should I do first...? Hmm... Okay, MEIKO, I choose you!
MEIKO: Hm? Me?
Rin: Yeah! “Thank you for always helping me whenever I'm in trouble!”
Rin: “Not only do you run our practices really well, you even go all out when we're having fun together! I really love how reliable and full of energy you are☆”
MEIKO: Hehe. Are these hearts a representation of just how much you love me?
Rin: Bingo! And this smiley face is you!
MEIKO: Thank you, Rin. Please feel free to ask me for help whenever.
Rin: Hehe♪
Saki: Alright, next...
Shiho: I think I'm up. Ready, Honami?
Honami: Y-Yes, I'm ready!
Shiho: There's no need to feel so anxious.
Shiho: Anyway... I wanted to make you something that you'd really like, but as expected, they didn't exactly have an apple pie-shaped card or pie stickers.
Shiho: So, I decided to use masking tape to get something close. Take a look.
Honami: Wow...! You really made this, Shiho?
Shiho: “You always keep a close eye on those around you and have their best interests at heart.”
Shiho: “There's probably a lot of good that you've done that I don't even know about.”
Shiho: “I firmly believe that we were only able to get this far because of you, Honami. Please keep being the great leader that you are.”
Honami: Shiho...
Honami: I really appreciate you saying all this, Shiho. And this card you made for me is so beautiful...
Honami: Thank you. I promise to treasure it forever.
Len: This feels like a great way to enjoy your youth.
Luka: Yes, I feel like writing some thank-you messages too now.
Saki: Hehe. Then, we can pass out the rest later. For now, let's start making our cards!
Rin: Let us know if you have any questions♪
Shiho: We also brought decorative pens and such, so feel free to use them as you like.
KAITO: Umm... So many choices... I don't know which to pick...
Saki: Choosing a recipient will make that a lot easier. For example, for Miku's card...
Saki: Captain Emu! At last, it's only us in this classroom!
Emu: Excellent! Then...
Saki & Emu: It's time for our after-party!
Shiho: Keep it down. There might still be people staying after school in the other classrooms.
Saki: Okay!
Saki: I brought a ton of snacks! Have as much as you like!
Emu: And I brought the juice! So, get your glasses ready!
Emu: Alright, cheers!
Saki & Shiho: Cheers! Cheers.
Saki: Oh, Emu, that reminds me. Did you get a chance to give Tsukasa and the others their cards?
Emu: Yup! I told them lots and lots about how much I appreciate them! How about you two, Saki?
Saki: We also passed out our cards! And afterwards, we made some more together.
Shiho: But it took a while to write our messages, since we were making cards for literally everyone.
Emu: Oh, that sounds really fun☆
Saki: It was! But I actually still have two cards left to give...
Emu: Oh, I also still have two! What about you, Shiho?
Shiho: Same... I mean, do we really need to make a big show of this?
Saki: Hehe♪ Then, I'll start with... My card for you, Emu!
Emu: Okay!
Saki: “You have a talent for cheering people up and making everyone around you smile, Emu.”
Saki: “That's why I always have fun whenever I'm with you. During our shadowing and while we helped out with the event, I was smiling the whole time because of you.”
Saki: “And I really admire how hard you're working to make your dream a reality.”
Saki: “I wouldn't have learned as much as I did about how these sorts of events are run if it weren't for you, Emu!”
Saki: “So, thank you for this wonderful experience! I hope we get to do more stuff like this in the future!”
Emu: Hehehe... Oh no... I don't know what to say... I feel so happy...
Emu: Thanks for this, Saki! Next, Shiho, it's my turn to give you your card!
Emu: “I really admire how cool and collected you always are, Shiho.”
Emu: “But the way you smile whenever you look at something cute is also really adorable! The expression you make is so nice.”
Shiho: ...
Emu: “Even during our shadowing, you stayed focused and made sure our discussion went smoothly.”
Emu: “I love how you're both really serious and really nice, Shiho! Thank you for always being such an amazing person☆”
Shiho: You're welcome.
Shiho: Alright, I guess this means... I'm giving you my card next, Saki?
Saki: Yup!
Shiho: “We've known each other forever and been through a lot...”
Shiho: “And you've become the person who best knows how to get me to go places and do stuff.”
Shiho: “I don't like wasting time, which usually means I push off taking breaks or hanging out with everyone...”
Shiho: “But you know how to get me to do it. There were times when I just went along to make you stop begging me...”
Shiho: “Still, I usually end up enjoying whatever we do wherever we go. Our shadowing and that event we helped out with included.”
Shiho: You get worked up really easily, so I try not to say this too often...
Shiho: But thank you for always taking me around places, Saki. You too, Otori.
Saki: Thanks for saying that, Shiho!
Emu: Time for a thank you group hug!
Shiho: Wait, don't throw yourselves at me like that.
Shiho: *Sigh* This is exactly what I was afraid of...
Saki: Hehe♪ It's your fault for saying what you did.
Emu: All's well that ends well☆
Shiho: I'm not sure that's the phrase I'd use...
Shiho: Anyway, I hope we get to keep doing stuff together.
Saki & Emu: Us too!
Saki: (I'm so glad we got to visit the same company together. I feel like we're a lot closer to each other now.)
Saki: (And I'm really glad that I got this chance to show them just how much I appreciate them.)
Saki: (Because now I understand that us all being together is sort of a miracle...)
Saki: (So, I'm gonna make sure to thank them as much as I can moving forward!)
